	<div itemprop="text"><p>True. Also, the joins in this case are relatively fast, since all the relevant fields being joined are indexed. Using a LIKE or similar is problematic because that causes a full table scan, which is slow if you have big tables. But indexed joins can be done very efficiently in most cases.</p>
</div>

