	<div itemprop="text"><p>What does the &#8216;field&#8217; do?  I&#8217;m really only trying to query one taxonomy and order the resulting posts by another. Can I query using the &#8216;tax_query&#8217; code above with only the &#8216;taxonomy&#8217; =&gt; &#8216;mytax&#8217; query?  will it pull all the posts in that tax?  or do I need to specify a term &amp; field?  I think thats a simple yes.  </p>
<p>My other question is a little more difficult.  If I have all the posts assigned a custom &#8216;date&#8217; tax (for events happening on that particular date), how can I order them by that date?<br />
I have this so far:
<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate" title="">$args['tax_query'] = array(
	 array (
		'taxonomy' =&gt; 'category',
		'terms'  =&gt;  'group_tours',
		),
	array (
		'taxonomy' =&gt; 'tour_dates',
	),
	'orderby' =&gt; 'name',
	'order' =&gt; 'asc',
	);</pre>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/wordpress-3-1-advanced-taxonomy-queries/comment-page-1/?replytocom=6343#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-6343", "6343", "respond", "331")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
