	<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-6346" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-6346" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/16ed25a57ebf7b4e53a646f73cb2594f?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://desperatelyseekingwp.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Cathy</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-1-advanced-taxonomy-queries/comment-page-1/#comment-6346">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2010-12-28T19:38:52+00:00">December 28, 2010 at 7:38 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>Thanks very much for your reply.  I realize after posting that the logic is wrong for ordering.  But if I assign a term to a post, isn&#8217;t it then &#8216;part of the post&#8217; and available (through some php magic) for ordering? Or by &#8216;part of the post&#8217; &#8211; I can find which parts by looking in the post table, right?</p>
