	<li class="comment even depth-2 parent" id="comment-7645" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-7645" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/d22c48810052c48be3559293fa07f85f?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name"><a itemprop='url' href='http://scribu.net' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>scribu</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-1-advanced-taxonomy-queries/comment-page-1/#comment-7645">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-03-15T19:30:01+00:00">March 15, 2011 at 7:30 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>It&#8217;s not working because you have to nest it in another array:</p>
<p>&#8216;tax_query&#8217; =&gt; array(<br />
  array(<br />
    &#8216;taxonomy&#8217; =&gt; &#8216;project-category&#8217;,<br />
    &#8216;terms&#8217; =&gt; array(&#8216;interaktywne&#8217;, &#8216;multimedialne&#8217;, &#8216;wideo&#8217;, &#8216;inne&#8217;),<br />
    &#8216;field&#8217; =&gt; &#8216;slug&#8217;<br />
  )<br />
)</p>
<p>Since it&#8217;s a single taxonomy you&#8217;re dealing with, it would be easier to write it like this:</p>
<p>  &#8216;project-category&#8217; =&gt; &#8216;interaktywne,multimedialne,wideo,inne&#8217;</p>
</div>

	<div class="reply">
	<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2010/wordpress-3-1-advanced-taxonomy-queries/comment-page-1/?replytocom=7645#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-7645", "7645", "respond", "331")'>Reply to this comment</a>	</div>
		</div>
	<ul class="children">
	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-otto bypostauthor odd alt depth-3" id="comment-7646" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-7646" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
