	<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-9644" itemprop="comment" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Comment">
		<div id="div-comment-9644" class="comment-body">
		<div class="comment-author" itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
	<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/f7d753cc8f24d8f4acc0bd1a1b6a723b?s=48&amp;d=retro&amp;r=X' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />	<cite itemprop="name">jared</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>	</div>

	<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a itemprop="url" href="http://ottopress.com/2010/wordpress-3-1-advanced-taxonomy-queries/comment-page-1/#comment-9644">
		<time itemprop="dateCreated" datetime="2011-09-06T18:43:21+00:00">September 6, 2011 at 6:43 pm</time></a>	</div>

	<div itemprop="text"><p>So i&#8217;m not much of a coder myself, but i was able to get my taxonomy query working and pagination as well.  in an attempt to help anyone else with the same problem I had, here&#8217;s my code.
<pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate" title="">&lt;?php

// List posts by the terms for a custom taxonomy of any post type
$paged = (get_query_var('paged')) ? get_query_var('paged') : 1;

$args = array(
'paged'=&gt;$paged,
	'tax_query' =&gt; array(
		array(
			'taxonomy'=&gt;'children',
			'field'=&gt;'slug',
			'paged'=&gt;$paged,
			'posts_per_page'=&gt;-1,
			'terms'=&gt;get_terms('children','fields=names')
		)
	)
);

		$temp = $wp_query;
		$wp_query = new WP_Query($args);
			$wp_query-&gt;query($args);
			
		if( $wp_query-&gt;have_posts() ) : ?&gt;

		&lt;?php while ( $wp_query-&gt;have_posts() ) : $wp_query-&gt;the_post(); ?&gt;
</pre>
<p>Thanks for everyone who helped.</p>
</div>

